<p>If you tap on paper-icon-button on its sides (i.e. not exactly in the centre), it goes into pressed state and "on-tap" event is not called. This is easily reproducible on chrome browser on touch devices.</p>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/Uk7ai.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/Uk7ai.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>  <p>Is there a workaround?</p>